    "analysis": "You computed global P95 thresholds for metric KPIs of candidate components (primarily adservice and frontend variants) using the full metric timeseries, then inspected the incident window (2022-03-21 06:00–06:29:59 UTC+8). Results show multiple small but consistent breaches in adservice JVM, gRPC, and OS KPIs (each series had 30 points; most had 2 breach points in-window). The largest relative deviation observed was adservice runtime.java_lang_OperatingSystem_SystemLoadAverage (ratio ≈ 1.41) with earliest breach at 06:05. Error logs show frontend-1 and frontend-2 repeatedly logged 'failed to retrieve ads', suggesting frontends experienced ad retrieval failures. At this stage metrics point to adservice abnormalities (JVM/CPU/load/gRPC) and error logs point to frontends failing to fetch ads. To decide root cause (frontend vs adservice vs node-level), we must analyze traces to see whether frontend→adservice calls show elevated error_rate or latency coincident with adservice metric breaches, and whether the frontends are the callers or victims. No trace-level thresholding has been done yet.",
